         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Newyears eve 1869. ¶  ¶ I regret very much to hear of your indisposition, dear Mr Bentham, ¶  but trust as you are so entirely your own master, that you can and will give yourself all the rest and att...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">69.12.31</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To George Bentham</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, f. 417.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Newyears eve 1869.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I regret very much to hear of your indisposition, dear Mr Bentham,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">Sciatica; see G. Bentham to M, 25 November 1869.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> but trust as you are so entirely your own master, that you can and will give yourself all the rest and attention, which at your age so much more than in former years is needed for the preservation of your vigor &amp; health. We cannot afford to have you long an invalid; so you must always take early care at the approaching danger of any illness.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am working on <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name>. The reduction of the species will be very great. I have done also a little among the Grasses of late. Thus I shall get the <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name> gradually into order for you. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The enclosed <name key="Prostanthera">Prostanthera</name> may only be a variety of one of the simple-leaved species, just like <name key="Teucrium%20racemosum">Teucrium racemosum</name> produces a three lobed variety.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">With best wishes for the new year </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Liliaceae">Liliaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Monocotyledoneae">Monocotyledoneae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
